      "content": "okay so u say it depends on what u prioritize, but in a real debate, isn't there a hierarchy? like, if a country's laws are being ignored by desperate people, does the law actually \"outweigh\" a human life? or is it fundamentally broken to prioritize borders over survival? i need a definitive way to frame which one is the \"higher\" moral ground so i can win the round.",
